# Assignment-MasterO-Backend


# Project Setup Steps

Step 1. npm install

Step 2. run dbInit.js to initialise the mysql database.

Step 3. run the app using npm start.

Note: Define PORT and Secret Key in environment file.

# Api Usage

AUTH : 

Register : METHOD - POST
           Endpoint - http://localhost:5000/auth/register

Login :    METHOD - POST
           Endpoint - http://localhost:5000/auth/login
           A token will be generated after the successfull login. Set the token in Authorization Type Bearer Token. ( POSTMAN )

Tasks : 
           METHOD :   POST
           Endpoint - http://localhost:5000/tasks
           Usage - Creates a task which can be assigned to a user.
           Body - { title, description, assigned_to, due_date }

           METHOD: GET
           Endpoint - http://localhost:5000/tasks 
           Usage - Fetches all the tasks
           Note - Only Authorized to Admin Users

           METHOD: GET
           Endpoint - http://localhost:5000/tasks/:id
           Usage - Get Task by TaskID

           METHOD: PUT
           Endpoint - http://localhost:5000/tasks/:id
           Usage - Update { title, description, status} of any task
           Note  - Only Authorized to Admin Users. But Employee can update their task status.


USERS :   METHOD: GET
          Endpoint - http://localhost:5000/users
          Usage - Fetches all the users of the application.
          Note - Only Authorized to Admin Users.
